<HEADLINE>
FT  13 SEP 94 / UK Company News: UK Safety tops Pounds 1m at midway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK Safety, the specialist footwear manufacturer, reported pre-tax profits of
Pounds 1.02m on turnover of Pounds 15.3m for the six months to July 2.
The outcome compared with a profit of Pounds 302,000 on turnover of Pounds
5.02m for the 1992 first half. Last year's interim figures however consist
of only two months' trading of the group in its present form.
The company came to the market in May last year through the reverse takeover
of TSW, the former independent television contractor for the south-west of
England.
Mr Colin Dunmore, chairman, said the outcome had been achieved against a
background of uneven demand and a competitive marketplace.
The figures had also been depressed by higher net interest costs of Pounds
464,000, against positive income of Pounds 81,000 received on the large TSW
cash balances last time, Mr Dunmore said.
In addition, the first phase of the group's restructuring plans had led to
an exceptional cost of Pounds 215,000, although this had been more than
offset by a Pounds 730,000 profit on the disposal of its investment in Socit
Europenne des Satellites, he added.
Earnings per share emerged at 1.78p (1.96p) and the interim dividend is
being maintained at 1.04p.
</TEXT>
