business, which Northern had been trying to sell for two years.
The company, which raised Pounds 2.4m via an intermediaries offer of
ordinary shares, said at the time that it was looking for opportunities that
either had above average possibilit-ies for medium term growth, or were
likely to generate steady but increasing income.
Yesterday the shares closed at 21.5p, up 1p.
