FT  13 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Scientific side behind drop at FII
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite an improved second half, FII Group, maker and distributor of
footwear and scientific and medical equipment, reported a fall in pre-tax
profits from Pounds 5.2m to Pounds 2.55m in the year ended May 31.
The result was after exceptional items of Pounds 1.32m (Pounds 550,000)
relating to product recall costs, losses on cancellation of a development
contract and rationalisation costs.
Turnover edged ahead to Pounds 83m (Pounds 82m) which Mr Monty Sumray, the
chairman, said was despite setbacks in the scientific and technical division
where sales fell to Pounds 8.45m (Pounds 11.3m). Rationalisation and
investment programmes were continuing in the division which reported losses
of Pounds 1.47m (Pounds 89,000).
In footwear, sales rose to a record Pounds 74.6m (Pounds 70.6m) although
operating profits slipped to Pounds 3.49m (Pounds 4.93m).
Earnings per share fell from 22.7p to 10.9p but the dividend is maintained
at 14.75p with an unchanged final of 8.75p.
