FT  13 SEP 94 / Russians testing water bomber
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL BETTS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Russians have been pouring cold water on Salisbury Plain with a
demonstration of a giant water bomber aircraft designed to combat the
growing scourge of forest fires, Paul Betts writes.
The demonstration of the Ilyushin IL-76, capable of carrying more than 40
tonnes of payload, was staged for the US Forest Service. The service is
interested in strengthening its fire fighting resources after the
devastating Californian fires last year.
The IL-76 is normally used for military transport and civil cargo.
Variants of the aircraft have also been built as aerial tankers for
refuelling military aircraft and as flying radar stations.
