<HEADLINE>
FT  13 SEP 94 / World Trade News: Czech-German rail move
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VINCENT BOLAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Czech Railways and Deutsche Bahn, its German equivalent, are to begin
transporting freight trucks on roll on-roll off trains across the
Czech/German border from September 25 in an attempt to speed up journey
times and lower costs, writes Vincent Boland in Prague. The service will run
on the 110km rail link between Dresden and the Czech town of Lovosice, 65km
north of Prague. It will initially carry 25 trucks daily but is expected to
be able to transport a quarter of the estimated 2,000 freight vehicles that
cross the border each day. The journey time will be 2 1/2 hours, with
continuous customs facilities, at a cost of DM85 (Dollars 54) per journey.
</TEXT>
