Swedes greeted his scheme to merge Volvo with Renault, is confidently
stressing the international credentials of the outfit which he is to chair.
With the likes of Francois-Xavier Ortoli, a former French finance minister
and EU commission president, and Lord Carrington, the former British foreign
secretary, it will doubtless prove an interesting cross-cultural exercise.
The European Merchant Bank, or however the London West End creature is
eventually styled, is contemplating a market that is far from saturated. It
will of course attract the envy of erstwhile colleagues strung up in the
bureaucracy of established investment banks.
So if Rudloff can be as tough with his cronies as he was with his CSFB
staff, he and PG could just be back on the road.
